SIMPLE: wike
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wike
<hw>Wike</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A temporary mark or
boundary, as a bough of a tree set up in marking out or dividing
anything, as tithes, swaths to be mowed in common ground, etc.; --
called also <altname>wicker</altname>.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wike</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wike
<hw>Wike</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>wic</ets>. See <er>Wick</er>
a village.]</ety> <def>A home; a dwelling.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wikiup</ent>⟦br⟧
